# LLM configuration for tag suggestions
#
# The CLI supports any OpenAI-compatible API: Ollama, LM Studio, OpenAI, vLLM, etc.
#
# If nothing is configured, it auto-detects a local Ollama (port 11434) or LM Studio (port 1234).

# --- Option 1: Local Ollama (auto-detected, no config needed) ---
# Just run `ollama serve`. Or be explicit:
# LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# LLM_MODEL=llama3

# --- Option 2: Local LM Studio (auto-detected, no config needed) ---
# Start LM Studio's local server. Or be explicit:
# LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1
# LLM_MODEL=your-loaded-model

# --- Option 3: OpenAI ---
# LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# LLM_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key
# LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# --- Option 4: Any OpenAI-compatible endpoint ---
# LLM_BASE_URL=https://your-endpoint/v1
# LLM_API_KEY=your-key
# LLM_MODEL=your-model

# --- Content limit for LLM prompts ---
# Max chars of page content sent to the LLM (default: 12000)
# Increase if your model has a large context window (e.g. 32K+)
# LLM_MAX_CHARS=12000
